<h3><strong><span class="blue">Key Discussion Points - January 2026</span></strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>CoreDNS Latency Crisis (RUN-115998 &amp; RUN-116253):</strong> Two Sev 1 incidents within 3 days revealed that the initial fix (scaling CoreDNS) was not the true root cause. The actual issue was DNS query amplification from Kubernetes ndots=5 behavior combined with increased Logstash activity from the Swagit release. The definitive fix was a CoreDNS regex rewrite rule, confirmed by remove-and-reapply testing.</li>
<li><strong>Certificate Management Process Gap (RUN-115814):</strong> The Helo encoder SSL certificate renewal revealed an undocumented non-standard requirement &mdash; the PEM must contain both the public certificate AND the private key. This process needs to be documented to prevent future incidents.</li>
<li><strong>Traffic Spike Handling:</strong> Multiple incidents (SpeakUp RUN-116311, OneMeeting CVRD RUN-115672) highlighted gaps in handling sudden legitimate traffic surges. Autoscaling assessments needed for both SpeakUp nodes and OneMeeting IIS pools.</li>
<li><strong>Third-Party Dependency Monitoring:</strong> The iLegislate incident (RUN-115749) revealed a dependency on joliet.granicus.com:443 that went 100% unavailable with no existing monitoring. Need to identify and monitor critical external dependencies.</li>
</ul>
